ODE VIII.

The Ode is written for an expected or imagined visit of Maecenas, on the first anniversary of the poet's narrow escape from the falling tree (2. 13, 2. 17. 27, 3. 4. 27). The festival of March 1 was the Matronalia. Maecenas is supposed on his entry to wonder what can be the reason that a bachelor's home shows preparation for sacrifice on such a day. The answer is. that the poet is paying a vow to Bacchus, which he had made · at the time of his miraculous preservation. ‘ The best wine is to be brought out,5 and so the Ode passes into an invitation to Maecenas to
